reviews.review_text: Near the end of Brent Not the best show as the age shows on everyone including jerry and bob. Kind of haunting it is so close to the end of Brent's life and excellent career in my opinion. Still an enjoyable show but definetly makes one consider the fragile nature of life. God bless Brent and Jerry!
Best Desolation Row Ever The five star rating is just for this version of Desolation Row, I've heard many versions and this one can not be beat!

Been saying the same thing since 1991...... This is THE all time great version of Desolation Row.  I know Alpine Valley 89 is often compared, but this one from Deer Creek 1990 beats it by a mile, IMO.

Heartland Dead This is one of my favs that I attended. We had it so good back then from '87-'90. There were some moments after the summer of '90 but never really as consitent as these tours. 
Jack Straw and Althea are the highlights for me and the end of NFA reminds me of an era we never wanted to end.
